Johannesburg - The African National Congress Youth League (ANCYL) eThekwini Region wants the police to probe Economic Freedom Fighters' (EFF) leader Julius Malema, who is seen in a video clip firing a gun in the air at a rally. 

In the video, which has gone viral, Malema who was dancing with other officials on a stage grabs a rifle that was leaning against the wall and fires it in the air. 
"It is the considered view of the ANC Youth League that this behaviour was unsafe, irresponsible and was also in contravention of section 120(7) of the Firearms Control Act of 2000," said the youth league on Wednesday in a statement attributed to its eThekwini region spokesperson, Thulisa Ndlela.   

 







